Oh, right. Good.

02:38.300 --> 02:41.300
- So what do ya got?
- Mini epidemic here in L.A.

02:41.300 --> 02:43.400
Eleven children between
the ages of five and eight...

02:43.400 --> 02:45.800
hospitalized due to collapse
over the last three weeks.

02:45.800 --> 02:47.700
None of them have woken up.

02:47.700 --> 02:50.800
I'm working under the assumption
that this thing is mystical in nature.

02:50.800 --> 02:53.600
Why's that?

02:53.600 --> 02:57.000
Right.
Could be TheJoker.

02:58.400 --> 03:00.800
From the comic books?

03:00.800 --> 03:03.000
Just tryin' to think
outside the box.

03:08.100 --> 03:12.800
<i>I know Valentine's was last week, but, um,</i>
<i>I didn't take the discount on the card.</i>

03:14.000 --> 03:18.300
Thanks. Um,
we talked about this.

03:18.300 --> 03:22.700
I was thinking maybe
we could talk about it again.

03:22.700 --> 03:27.500
[Sighs]
I'm sorry, Knox, but you have work to do.

03:31.900 --> 03:34.100
I do.

03:35.500 --> 03:38.800
<i>[Indistinct Chattering]</i>

03:42.700 --> 03:45.800
[Guttural Squawks]

03:48.200 --> 03:50.300
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:50.300 --> 03:52.500
Back for the Wolfram and Hart
Bed and Breakfast?

03:52.500 --> 03:56.300
Full moon cycle starts tonight.
In 38 minutes, actually.

03:56.300 --> 03:58.300
Had a little snag
getting out of the house.

03:58.300 --> 04:02.100
- Haven't told your sister yet?
- Not the sort of thing
that's easy to jump to in conversation.

04:02.100 --> 04:05.000
"Oh, by the way, Jill,
I've been a werewolf for four months."

04:05.000 --> 04:07.500
I told her I was going camping
in the desert again.

04:07.500 --> 04:12.200
She's starting to worry I've turned into
some New Agey, moon-worshipping Wicca person.

04:12.200 --> 04:14.300
Might be relieved to find out
you're just a werewolf.

04:14.300 --> 04:16.800
- Hey there, Nina. We've got your suite ready.
- It's okay, Harmony.

04:16.800 --> 04:18.899
- I'll take her.
- Bye.

04:18.899 --> 04:22.600
<i>Harmony, did you get a receipt</i>
<i>from the county clerk...</i>

04:22.600 --> 04:25.100
on that filing I did
for the Wayburn case?

04:25.100 --> 04:28.500
Oh, yeah. Clerk's office called,
said you filed the wrong papers.

04:28.500 --> 04:30.500
- What?
- Yeah.

04:30.500 --> 04:35.300
You sent them a motion for change of venue
instead of a motion to dismiss.

04:35.300 --> 04:37.800
Unless you meant to do that...

04:37.800 --> 04:40.500
some kind of tricky lawyer maneuvering
you're trying to pull.

04:40.500 --> 04:44.800
- That it?
- Yeah. Keep 'em on their toes.

04:47.600 --> 04:50.300
Seems like you're gettin' used
to the routine though.

04:50.300 --> 04:53.300
Yeah. In a weird way,
I'm starting to like it.

04:53.300 --> 04:58.200
These stay-overs, I mean. Not the going
all hairy part, but... I don't know... coming here.

04:58.200 --> 05:03.300
There's always something interesting
going on... and getting to see you.

05:03.300 --> 05:06.700
<i>I look forward to that... you.</i>

05:06.700 --> 05:11.700
- All month, actually.
- Uh, um, I should probably close the cage.

05:11.700 --> 05:13.700
What?

05:13.700 --> 05:17.000
- Insurance thing.
- Oh, right.

05:17.000 --> 05:19.900
Okay. Um, bye.

05:19.900 --> 05:22.800
Anyway, I was thinking...

05:22.800 --> 05:26.200
I mean, what are you doing
for breakfast tomorrow?

05:27.600 --> 05:30.500
Oh, you know...
drinkin' blood.

05:30.500 --> 05:33.100
Right. Yeah.

05:33.100 --> 05:35.600
Uh, see ya.

05:37.800 --> 05:40.300
<i>- [Angel] She asked me to breakfast.</i>
- Breakfast?

05:41.500 --> 05:43.400
Right.

05:43.400 --> 05:45.700
How did you respond?

05:45.700 --> 05:50.300
Well, of course, I... [Clears Throat]
Ignored it completely...

05:50.300 --> 05:53.500
changed the subject
and locked her in a cage.

05:53.500 --> 05:56.400
- Sorry. What?
- Wes, it wasn't just breakfast.

05:56.400 --> 05:59.800
You know, it was...
<i>breakfast.</i>

05:59.800 --> 06:04.400
We had this very good, platonic thing goin' on,
and then all of a sudden, out of the blue...

06:04.400 --> 06:08.000
Are you blind?
Angel, there are things called signals.

06:08.000 --> 06:11.500
Odorless, yes. Invisible, certainly.
But unmistakable.

06:11.500 --> 06:15.400
- Like the ones she's been
casting your way for months.
- No. I would've noticed.

06:15.400 --> 06:18.300
This isn't just from me.
This comes from people who know.

06:18.300 --> 06:20.600
- This comes from the ladies.
- The ladies?

06:20.600 --> 06:23.400
Fred, Harmony,
the girls in transcription.

06:23.400 --> 06:27.200
<i>As Harmony put it,</i>
<i>"Why else would a chick...</i>

06:27.500 --> 06:31.500
who's coming to spend three nights
in a jail cell dress like it's her first date?"

06:31.500 --> 06:35.500
Oh, God.
The ladies are right.

06:35.500 --> 06:40.100
Nina's down there right now
turning into a werewolf and liking me.

06:40.100 --> 06:43.800
I don't... I can't...
I have no time for that kind of...

06:43.800 --> 06:47.200
I have no right. I mean, look.
We all know what happens if...

06:47.200 --> 06:51.600
If what? If you achieve a moment
of perfect happiness?

06:51.600 --> 06:54.000
- I turn back into Angelus, and we don't want that.
- [Scoffs]

06:54.000 --> 06:59.100
- What?
- 99.999 ad infinitum percent...

06:59.100 --> 07:01.900
of the best relationships
in the recorded history of the world...

07:01.900 --> 07:04.500
have had to make do
with acceptable happiness.

07:04.500 --> 07:07.200
- Look, Wes...
- Hiding behind your gypsy curse
when there's a beautiful...

07:07.200 --> 07:11.100
<i>engaging... all right,</i>
<i>occasionally hirsute... young woman...</i>

07:11.400 --> 07:13.300
who actually wants you?

07:13.300 --> 07:16.700
- Wes, it's not gonna happen.
- Why?
- Because I'm not that guy.

07:16.700 --> 07:21.500
That guy is charming
and funny and... emotionally useful.

07:21.500 --> 07:25.900
I'm the guy in the dark corner with the blood habit
and the 200 years of psychic baggage.

07:25.900 --> 07:28.100
- Get over it!
- Why are you yelling at me?

07:28.100 --> 07:30.700
Because!

07:30.700 --> 07:36.200
Angel, if there's a woman out there...

07:36.200 --> 07:38.900
who you find truly attractive...

07:38.900 --> 07:43.800
who you think about,
let's say, most of the time...

07:43.800 --> 07:48.100
who represents even part of what you think
makes the world worth fighting for...

07:48.100 --> 07:50.400
and who doesn't view you...

07:50.400 --> 07:54.700
as an entirely sexless shoulder
to lean on...

07:54.700 --> 07:58.400
you have to do something
about it.

07:59.800 --> 08:03.500
- Who are we talkin' about here?
- Fred.

08:03.500 --> 08:06.900
Hey, guys.
Uh, I think I have a case.

08:06.900 --> 08:10.400
- [In Unison] Thank God.
- A children's epidemic. Seven kids comatose...

08:10.400 --> 08:12.800
each with a semi-rictus
of the facial muscles.

08:12.800 --> 08:16.200
- I haven't been able to isolate a causative agent.
- You think it's mystical?

08:16.200 --> 08:20.800
Well, I've been down the strictly physiological
route, number-crunched victims' charts...

08:20.800 --> 08:23.800
even had our hospital contacts
send over blood samples.

08:23.800 --> 08:27.600
I've pulled their plasma apart. No indicators
on the cellular or subcellular levels.

08:27.900 --> 08:30.300
- TV.
- What?

08:30.300 --> 08:33.700
Parents said all the kids
collapsed between 7:00 and...

08:33.700 --> 08:36.500
it looks like 7:30 a.m.

08:36.500 --> 08:38.900
- And all of them in front of the TV.
- Hmm.

08:38.900 --> 08:43.299
That could be something. But I'd still
like to get a handle on the pathology.

08:43.299 --> 08:46.500
Good. I'll follow up on this lead.
I'll need to clear my schedule.

08:46.500 --> 08:49.200
These kids need help.

08:49.200 --> 08:52.600
[Chuckles]
Wow. He really jumped on that one.

08:52.600 --> 08:58.200
Yes. He is a bit jumpy.
He's realized Nina has feelings for him.

08:58.200 --> 09:01.100
- Well, it took long enough.
- He can be rather dense.

09:02.900 --> 09:06.900
Um, by the way,
my car is in the shop again...

09:07.100 --> 09:09.800
- and I was thinking...
- Of course.

09:09.800 --> 09:12.700
Maybe you and I,
we could...

09:12.700 --> 09:15.300
Yes. Miss Burkle needs a driver
to take her home tonight.

09:15.300 --> 09:19.900
<i>That's right.</i>
<i>511 Windward Circle.</i>

09:19.900 --> 09:22.900
<i>[Lorne] All the signals are there,</i>
<i>jefe, loud and clear.</i>

09:22.900 --> 09:27.900
- Nina definitely wants a piece of Angelcake.
- Can we get back to the job?

09:27.900 --> 09:30.200
Your wish, dreamboat,
my command.

09:30.200 --> 09:33.000
- [Groans]
<i>- I know most of the show runners</i>
<i>in town, and none of them...</i>

09:33.000 --> 09:37.000
are really up to this sort
of big-league, sinister...

09:37.100 --> 09:40.200
Hey. [Chuckles]
7:00 to 7:30?

09:40.200 --> 09:43.800
- Yeah.
- That'd be funny.

09:43.800 --> 09:46.000
- You know, if it wasn't.
- What?

09:46.000 --> 09:48.400
Real popular kids' show
in the SoCal regional market.

09:48.400 --> 09:52.900
<i>- It's in the right time slot,</i>
<i>the right demographic.</i>
- What's it called?

09:52.900 --> 09:56.300
<i>Smile Time.</i>

