- [Angel] Uh, Fred?
- Oh, hi, Angel.

13:13.500 --> 13:16.800
- About the epidemic. It might
not be mystical after all.
- Do you think you could...

13:16.800 --> 13:20.000
Knox found a systematic endocrine dysfunction
common with all the children...

13:20.000 --> 13:22.300
<i>- similar to the effects of</i>
<i>an obscure rain forest pathogen,</i>
- Fred?

13:22.300 --> 13:24.400
So I put a call in
to the C.D.C., and...

13:24.400 --> 13:28.100
Fred! Believe me,
it's mystical.

13:28.100 --> 13:30.800
<i>- [Door Opens]</i>
- Angel?

13:30.800 --> 13:33.600
- You all right?
- You sounded weird on the phone.

13:33.600 --> 13:37.200
<i>- [Wesley] Yes. Is there a problem?</i>
<i>- Oh, there's a problem.</i>

13:39.500 --> 13:42.000
Whoa.

13:42.000 --> 13:45.600
Angel? Is that you?

13:45.600 --> 13:48.900
Oh, my God!
Angel, you're...

13:48.900 --> 13:50.900
cute.

13:50.900 --> 13:55.200
- Fred, don't.
- Oh, but the little hands! And the hair.

13:55.200 --> 13:57.700
Hey! You're fired.

13:57.700 --> 14:02.200
Sorry I am late, gang, but...
What's with the big... puppet?

14:02.200 --> 14:05.500
- [Groaning]
- Angel, what happened?

14:05.500 --> 14:08.800
I'm not sure. I went over
to <i>Smile Time</i> last night.

14:08.800 --> 14:13.400
I think their office is under some kind
of spell. I could feel it trying to get at me.

14:13.400 --> 14:17.000
I shook it off, but then I met this guy
with a towel over his head...

14:17.000 --> 14:19.500
and something exploded.

14:19.500 --> 14:22.900
I woke up like this.

14:22.900 --> 14:26.100
Clearly some sort of hex...

14:26.100 --> 14:29.800
<i>or a powerful warding magic.</i>

14:29.800 --> 14:33.600
<i>- Maybe you have some type of puppet cancer.</i>
- I do not have puppet cancer!

14:33.900 --> 14:38.700
Come on, guys. This is serious.
I'm a puppet, and there are children's lives at...

14:38.700 --> 14:42.100
[Gasps]
Hey, it's <i>Smile Time.!</i>

14:50.000 --> 14:54.500
[Grunting]

14:54.500 --> 14:57.900
[Huffs]
Stupid plastic piece of crap!

14:57.900 --> 15:00.500
[Panting]
What?

15:00.500 --> 15:03.500
Angel, it's okay.

15:03.500 --> 15:07.300
<i>This transformation may have</i>
<i>altered your stress-response mechanism.</i>

15:07.600 --> 15:10.700
- What?
<i>- He's saying you have</i>
<i>the proportionate excitability...</i>

15:10.700 --> 15:12.600
of a puppet your size.

15:12.600 --> 15:14.700
<i>- [TV: Puppet] Oh, hey there.</i>
<i>- [Puppet</i> #<i>2] Hi.</i>

15:14.700 --> 15:19.200
- Oh, looks like Polo has a case of the grumpies.
- He sure does, Groofus...

15:19.200 --> 15:23.900
<i>and mean old Mr. Fish-and-Chips</i>
<i>said that Polo won't win the race tomorrow...</i>

15:23.900 --> 15:26.900
<i>- no matter how hard he tries.</i>
<i>- [Polo] Uh-huh.</i>

15:26.900 --> 15:32.000
- And I feel just awful. What if
Mr. Fish-and-Chips is right?
- [Squeaking]

15:32.000 --> 15:35.800
Tracy, record the program
that's running on channel 12 right now.

15:35.800 --> 15:39.200
Use everything.
I'm gonna need a full spectrum analysis.

15:39.200 --> 15:42.400
Self-esteem
is for everybody

15:42.400 --> 15:47.300
<i>Self-esteem</i>
<i>is for everyone</i>

