You can dream
and be anybody

15:50.400 --> 15:54.200
But self-esteem
is how you get it done

15:54.500 --> 15:57.400
<i>Self-esteem</i>
<i>is how you get it done</i>

15:57.400 --> 16:00.500
- Wes, put the special ops team on red alert.
- Red alert?

16:00.500 --> 16:02.900
I want helicopters and tear gas.
This is war!

16:02.900 --> 16:08.200
<i>Angel, baby, muppet, pumpkin,</i>
<i>this show is number one in its time slot.</i>

16:08.200 --> 16:12.000
Tykes love it all across the Southland.
We can't just toss a jihad at the studio.

16:12.000 --> 16:14.500
No. Right.
Lorne, who runs <i>Smile Time?</i>

16:14.500 --> 16:17.600
Oh, that's Gregor Framkin.
Yeah, real rags to riches.

16:17.600 --> 16:20.900
Started out in a garage with a couple
of used couches and a glue gun.

16:20.900 --> 16:23.600
He turned it
into a puppet gold mine.

16:23.600 --> 16:26.400
Yeah. Great. You and Gunn
go over and meet with Framkin...

16:26.400 --> 16:29.000
<i>put some pressure on him, see ifhe cracks,</i>
<i>let him know we're onto him.</i>

16:29.000 --> 16:33.900
Fred, Wes, I need you to figure out
what Framkin did to those kids and to me.

16:33.900 --> 16:37.100
<i>[Wesley]</i>
<i>Absolutely.</i>

16:37.100 --> 16:40.500
<i>- [On-screen Singing Continues]</i>
- [Angel Sighs] Oh, uh, guys...

16:40.500 --> 16:43.800
this condition of mine...

16:43.800 --> 16:47.600
It's classified
until further notice, okay?

16:51.700 --> 16:53.600
[Groans]

16:54.800 --> 16:57.600
Self-esteem
is for everybody

16:57.600 --> 17:01.600
<i>Self-esteem</i>
<i>is for everyone</i>

17:01.600 --> 17:05.599
<i>You can dream</i>
<i>and be anybody</i>

17:05.700 --> 17:09.099
<i>But self-esteem</i>
<i>is how you get it done</i>

17:09.099 --> 17:13.000
- [Nina] Angel?
- [Gasping]

17:19.000 --> 17:22.000
- Angel?
- [Grunting] Damn it!

17:23.599 --> 17:27.099
You... Are you
under your desk?

17:27.099 --> 17:29.700
No. L... Yes.

17:29.700 --> 17:33.700
<i>- So was there something...</i>
- Well, I can see you're...

17:33.800 --> 17:36.400
busy.

17:36.400 --> 17:39.500
Listen. What I
put out there last night...

17:39.500 --> 17:42.900
- I don't know. If it was a problem, please...
<i>- Nope. No problem.</i>

17:42.900 --> 17:48.300
Um, is there a reason
why you won't look at me?

17:48.300 --> 17:51.000
- 'Cause I'm under my desk.
- Angel...

17:51.000 --> 17:55.500
- Nina, would you mind getting out of here?
- All right.

17:55.500 --> 17:58.100
<i>Sorry, I guess.</i>

18:00.500 --> 18:03.200
[Sighs]

18:03.200 --> 18:05.600
[Grunting]
Nightmare.

18:07.100 --> 18:09.900
<i>- [Door Opens]</i>
<i>- [Spike] Hey, big guy.</i>

18:09.900 --> 18:13.900
Need another car. I'm afraid
this last one ended up in the drink.

18:14.000 --> 18:15.600
- Spike...
- Look at you.

18:15.600 --> 18:19.000
- Just turn around and walk away.
- You're a...

18:19.000 --> 18:21.100
- Spike!
- You're a bloody puppet!

18:22.700 --> 18:25.600
[Spike Giggling]

18:28.400 --> 18:33.100
You're a wee little puppet man!
[Laughing]

18:33.100 --> 18:35.100
Ow! Hey, that's enough.

18:37.400 --> 18:41.200
Angel, what the hell
happened to you?

18:41.200 --> 18:44.200
- You look ridiculous.
- Get out of here, Spike.

18:44.200 --> 18:46.300
- Oh, my God. Angel, you're a...
- Shut up.

18:50.000 --> 18:54.000
What are you people
lookin' at? Well?

18:55.900 --> 19:00.500
- They're lookin' at the wee little puppet man.
- [Growling]

19:00.500 --> 19:03.800
Whoa! Whoa. Whoa.

19:03.800 --> 19:06.300
[Spike Growling]

19:06.300 --> 19:09.300
[Spike Yelping]

19:09.300 --> 19:12.400
<i>[Angel]</i>
<i>Stupid limey piece of crap.!</i>

19:12.400 --> 19:15.800
<i>- [Spike Grunts]</i>
<i>- [Elevator Bell Dings]</i>

19:15.800 --> 19:17.900
[Sighs]

19:17.900 --> 19:21.800
Yes, I'm a puppet. It doesn't mean
you don't have work to do.

19:22.100 --> 19:24.500
[All Murmuring]

19:32.800 --> 19:35.500
Harmony, get my call list.

19:37.300 --> 19:40.300
- Um...
<i>- And Spike needs a car.</i>

19:40.300 --> 19:42.200
You heard the puppet.

19:45.200 --> 19:48.200
<i>- [Gunn] Mr. Framkin?</i>
<i>- [Door Closes]</i>

19:48.200 --> 19:50.600
Hi there. Oh.

19:50.600 --> 19:54.600
Excuse me for not getting up.
Bit glued in at the moment.

19:54.600 --> 19:57.700
Mr. Framkin, we've been tracking
an epidemic that's affecting a great many...

19:57.700 --> 19:59.700
- Cocoa?
- What?

19:59.700 --> 20:02.300
I can have some cocoa
brought in. Extra yummy.

20:02.300 --> 20:05.200
- Got those itty-bitty marshmallows.
- Ooh, those are good.

20:05.200 --> 20:09.000
Listen, Santa. You can keep your tempting
beverages to yourself. We're here from...

20:09.000 --> 20:11.400
Wolfram and Hart.
Yes. I've heard of it.

20:11.400 --> 20:14.500
And of you. You've made
quite an impression in our little industry.

20:14.500 --> 20:18.000
So much accomplishment
despite your unfortunate deformities.

20:18.000 --> 20:20.600
- Deformi-what?
- We have a song here at <i>Smile Time...</i>

20:20.600 --> 20:22.700
that reminds me
of your courage and pluck.

20:22.700 --> 20:26.700
<i>It's called "Courage and Pluck."</i>
<i>It goes a little like this:</i>

20:26.900 --> 20:29.100
Oh, courage and pluck
courage and pluck

20:29.100 --> 20:32.000
Okay, Framkin.
Enough. We're onto you, understand?

20:32.000 --> 20:36.400
- We're gonna shut you down.
- Oh, my. On what grounds?

20:36.400 --> 20:40.900
Well, for starters, violations
of the provisions of section five... five...

20:40.900 --> 20:45.600
<i>68-C set forth in chapter 15</i>
<i>of the children's...</i>

20:46.700 --> 20:48.700
TV thing.

20:48.700 --> 20:52.400
- You turned my boss into a frickin' puppet.
- I disagree.

20:52.400 --> 20:57.100
- Yeah, but... You what?
<i>- And if your intent is to pressure me...</i>

20:57.100 --> 21:00.900
extort money, do any of the things
your firm is famous for...

21:00.900 --> 21:03.600
well, I'm afraid
you're in for a fight.

21:03.600 --> 21:07.400
Yeah? Well,
a fight suits us just fine, Papa Smurf.

21:07.400 --> 21:10.000
<i>We're gonna let</i>
<i>the entire world know what you're up to.</i>

21:10.000 --> 21:13.400
"Up to"? Gentlemen,
I bring joy and laughter to children.

21:13.400 --> 21:19.000
You bring tax exemptions to
nasty corporations, acquittals to the guilty.

21:19.000 --> 21:21.500
Frankly, I doubt
the world wants to hear from you.

21:21.500 --> 21:24.400
Come on, Lorne. We're through
talkin' to this hump of garbage.

21:24.400 --> 21:26.500
Oop. No name-calling
at <i>Smile Time.</i>

21:26.500 --> 21:29.600
Bad person!

21:29.600 --> 21:32.800
- Buh-bye now.
<i>- [Door Closes]</i>

21:32.800 --> 21:35.500
[Humming <i>Smile Time</i> Theme]

21:42.100 --> 21:46.800
- [Sighs]
- [Numbers Beep]

21:46.800 --> 21:50.400
Get everybody in here.
We got a problem.

21:59.900 --> 22:03.800
Okay. Which one
of you short-bus bastards...

22:03.800 --> 22:06.300
turned the C.E.O.
Of Wolfram and Hart into a puppet?

22:06.300 --> 22:08.100
- Duh...
- [Squeaks]

22:08.100 --> 22:10.600
- What do you mean, it wasn't us?
- [Squeaks Phrase]

22:10.600 --> 22:16.000
Ratio's right. This Angel cat must have been
the dude that broke into the Don't Room.

22:16.000 --> 22:18.100
- [Squeaking]
- That's what I'm sayin'.

22:18.100 --> 22:20.200
He messed with the nest egg.

22:20.200 --> 22:24.000
Stupid jackass. Might as well walk
into a nuclear reactor and lick the core.

22:24.000 --> 22:27.000
<i>I mean, anything could've</i>
<i>happened to him, to us, to...</i>

22:27.000 --> 22:29.800
You just don't mess around
with the nest egg!

22:29.800 --> 22:32.300
Maybe we should take the spell
off a couple of our workers, you know...

22:32.300 --> 22:34.400
so they could actually
see an intruder?

22:34.400 --> 22:36.600
Yeah. Damn zombies
can't even work a camera.

22:36.600 --> 22:39.100
Doesn't matter. The nest egg's
already got enough power in it...

22:39.100 --> 22:42.900
to keep our cloaking spells up and running,
make our connections with the kiddies...

22:42.900 --> 22:44.800
even turn this Angel guy
into a puppet.

22:44.800 --> 22:47.100
Which is definitely
gonna bite us in the ass.

22:47.100 --> 22:49.300
Then we make sure our ass
ain't here to bite.

22:49.300 --> 22:52.700
- What?
<i>- Ratio has perfected our little system.</i>

22:52.700 --> 22:55.600
- [Squeaks]
- Tomorrow we go on the air, and instead of...

22:55.600 --> 22:58.000
draining one brat's life force
at a time...

22:58.000 --> 23:00.900
we can take out our whole demographic
in one fell swoop.

23:00.900 --> 23:04.800
- [All Exclaiming]
- So tomorrow's gonna be a pretty big show, huh?

23:04.800 --> 23:08.200
- The biggest.
- Cool. 'Cause I been workin'
on this great new song...

23:08.200 --> 23:11.500
<i>about the difference</i>
<i>between analogy and metaphor.</i>

23:11.500 --> 23:13.600
- Man!
- Are you out of your mind?

23:13.600 --> 23:16.900
- Well, we want it to be good, don't we?
- We eat babies' lives!

23:16.900 --> 23:19.900
And uphold a certain standard
of quality "edu-tainment."

23:19.900 --> 23:24.600
Screw "edu-tainment." The life force
we're pullin' out of these snot-nosed kids...

23:24.600 --> 23:26.900
is 100% pure innocence,
dick wad!

23:26.900 --> 23:29.300
You have any idea of the street value
that carries down in hell?

23:29.300 --> 23:31.800
- [Squeaks]
- Damn right we're gonna be rich.

23:31.800 --> 23:34.100
Enough to
build our very own Hades.

23:34.100 --> 23:37.100
- I gotta admit, I like the sound of that.
- Mm-hmm.

23:37.100 --> 23:40.000
<i>After tomorrow's harvest,</i>
<i>we're gonna torch this crap hole...</i>

23:40.000 --> 23:42.200
and blow town
before the rafters fall.

23:42.200 --> 23:44.300
[Rasping]
Please... let me...

23:44.300 --> 23:47.900
- Someone say you could join in?
- Let me die.

23:47.900 --> 23:50.000
- Ah.
<i>- [Polo] Ohh.</i>

23:50.000 --> 23:53.100
Are you sayin' you wanna
talk to the hand?

23:53.100 --> 23:55.600
<i>Oh, I think he does.</i>

23:55.600 --> 23:59.400
Come on, fat boy.
Why don't you talk to the hand?

23:59.400 --> 24:02.300
- [Screeching]
<i>- [Puppets Laughing]</i>

24:02.300 --> 24:06.300
- Make him swallow his tongue again.
- [Yelping]

24:06.400 --> 24:09.100
<i>[Puppets'Laughter Echoing]</i>

24:14.700 --> 24:17.700
<i>[Angel]</i>
<i>Uh, Nina?</i>

24:17.700 --> 24:19.800
Angel?

24:19.800 --> 24:22.900
Yeah. Sort of.

24:22.900 --> 24:28.500
Uh, listen. I wanna apologize
about the way I treated you this morning.

24:28.500 --> 24:31.200
- Look, Angel. I understand.
- I'm pretty sure you don't.

24:31.200 --> 24:34.500
You've got this whole
complicated, important life going on...

24:34.500 --> 24:38.800
and the last thing you need to deal with
is a crush from Monster Girl...

24:38.800 --> 24:41.500
some charity case
you were nice enough to...

24:41.500 --> 24:44.600
Nina...
[Sighs]

24:51.000 --> 24:54.500
- Oh.
- I was turned into a puppet last night.

24:56.400 --> 24:58.400
I, uh...

25:00.000 --> 25:02.000
Wow.

25:02.000 --> 25:05.700
<i>Are you... Are you okay?</i>

25:05.700 --> 25:07.500
I'm made of felt.

25:08.900 --> 25:10.700
[Nasal]
And my nose comes off.

25:14.900 --> 25:18.700
- I don't know what to say.
- My people are workin' on the problem.

25:18.700 --> 25:22.000
I'm sure they'll fix it...
eventually.

25:22.000 --> 25:24.100
[Sighs]

25:24.100 --> 25:28.500
I didn't mean to upset you this morning.
I just didn't want anyone...

25:28.500 --> 25:31.600
Well, I didn't want you
to see me this way.

25:31.600 --> 25:35.600
It's a little, uh,
embarrassing, I guess.

25:35.700 --> 25:39.200
I'd call it a little insane...

25:39.200 --> 25:44.000
but what do you care
what people think anyway?

25:44.000 --> 25:49.100
Angel, you're <i>you,</i> you know?

25:49.100 --> 25:53.700
You're this... I mean,
God, you're an actual hero.

25:53.700 --> 25:57.200
And, I don't know, this may sound cliché
coming from an art school chick...

25:57.200 --> 26:01.100
but the vampire thing's
kind of sexy.

26:01.100 --> 26:06.500
[Chuckles] It all sounds good,
but that's not how I feel.

26:06.500 --> 26:10.500
I know.
That's what I like about you.

26:13.300 --> 26:17.800
Yeah. I'm not very good
at any of this.

26:17.800 --> 26:21.800
[Sighs] I've spent so much time
worrying about the past...

26:22.000 --> 26:27.400
and the future
and my very complicated life.

26:27.400 --> 26:32.100
It's been a while since I've looked up
and really saw what was goin' on around me.

26:32.100 --> 26:36.800
It's not my strong suit,
you know, but I'm workin' on it.

26:36.800 --> 26:39.200
- I'm payin' better attention to...
<i>- [Growls]</i>

26:39.200 --> 26:43.700
Geez! No! No, Nina!
Bad Nina!

26:43.700 --> 26:45.600
[Screams]

26:49.600 --> 26:53.500
<i>[Grunting, Groaning]</i>
<i>Lorne.!</i>

26:53.500 --> 26:57.000
- My little prince!
- [Grunts]

26:57.000 --> 27:00.500
- [Panting]
- Ohh.

27:00.500 --> 27:03.900
- What did they do to you?
- Nina...

27:03.900 --> 27:06.700
tried to... eat me.

27:06.700 --> 27:09.500
Medic!
You're gonna make it, Angel.

27:09.500 --> 27:12.900
Just don't stop fighting.
Doctor!

27:12.900 --> 27:15.800
Is there a Geppetto
in the house?

27:15.800 --> 27:18.400
<i>[Electrical Arcing]</i>

27:22.900 --> 27:26.500
- [Knocking]
- Good. Good.

27:26.500 --> 27:29.400
With you in a minute.

27:29.400 --> 27:32.500
So, I want you
to keep those glasses on for a full week...

27:32.500 --> 27:34.400
give those fancy new retinas
time to adjust.

27:34.400 --> 27:38.900
See you in 14 days.
X-ray vision. Very now.

27:38.900 --> 27:42.600
- Something's wrong
with the implant you gave me.
- I doubt that. Gunn, isn't it?

27:43.600 --> 27:46.600
Well, let's take a look.

27:46.600 --> 27:51.200
[Humming]
Ah. The imprint is fading. Don't blink.

27:51.200 --> 27:54.400
The neural path modification
has almost completely reverted.

27:54.400 --> 27:57.800
I'm losin' it.
The law. The languages. The strategy.

27:57.800 --> 28:00.700
Acute <i>Flowers for Algernon</i>
syndrome.

28:00.700 --> 28:04.700
- It must be sheer torture.
- Well, fix it. Put it back.

28:04.900 --> 28:07.900
Well, no offense, counselor...

28:07.900 --> 28:11.200
but your insurance plan wouldn't cover
what I charge to wash my hands.

28:11.200 --> 28:14.900
You were given that upgrade 'cause
the senior partners wanted you to have it.

28:14.900 --> 28:18.500
And if you're losing it,
well, they wanted that too.

28:18.500 --> 28:22.900
- Why would they do that?
- [Chuckles] You never know with them.

28:22.900 --> 28:26.400
I can't lose this...
this power, these skills.

28:26.400 --> 28:30.700
- They've changed me, given me...
- Meaning?

28:30.700 --> 28:34.500
And to have it taken away...
It's heartbreaking.

28:34.500 --> 28:38.100
Though I do think Cliff Robertson captured
the poignance of it more elegantly.

28:38.100 --> 28:42.700
- I'm not goin' back to who I was.
- Well, maybe, maybe not.

28:45.300 --> 28:50.100
See, I, uh... I always have
a few things going on the side.

28:50.100 --> 28:52.400
- [Machine Beeping]
- Currently I have a lot...

28:52.400 --> 28:55.500
of capital sunk into a shipment
that's being held up at Customs.

28:55.500 --> 28:58.800
- Drugs?
- [Chuckles] Goodness, no. I make my own drugs.

28:58.800 --> 29:02.700
No. Just an ancient curio...
a collectible I hope to turn a profit on.

29:02.700 --> 29:07.100
If I was to give you
the permanent upgrade...

29:07.100 --> 29:10.600
I'd say that you'd be more than able
to cut through all of my red tape problems.

29:10.600 --> 29:12.300
I don't make deals
with people like you.

29:12.300 --> 29:15.100
Believe me, Charles.
I don't make deals with people like <i>you.</i>

29:15.100 --> 29:19.100
Not the person you really are...
the ignorant street muscle.

29:19.300 --> 29:22.400
<i>The high school dropout.</i>
<i>I would, however...</i>

29:22.400 --> 29:26.200
Iove to make a deal
with Charles Gunn, attorney at law.

29:29.200 --> 29:32.500
And now it's time
for Action Math News...

29:32.500 --> 29:37.400
with your Action Math experts,
Ratio Hornblower and Groofus.

29:37.400 --> 29:40.100
[Ratio Whooping]

29:40.100 --> 29:44.000
Thank you, Polo.
Our top story this morning.

29:44.000 --> 29:46.800
Two plus two is four.

29:46.800 --> 29:52.000
And in related news,
four plus four is eight!

29:52.000 --> 29:55.500
It could be
the lack of sleep talking, but...

29:55.500 --> 29:57.900
I'm really starting
to like this show.

29:57.900 --> 30:02.400
I know what you mean.
What time is it?

30:02.400 --> 30:05.800
4:00 a.m. And counting.

30:08.000 --> 30:10.500
- Oh, I'm sorry. Did you want...
- Ah, it's all right.

30:10.500 --> 30:13.200
<i>- 'Cause I could...</i>
- No. Really.

30:13.200 --> 30:15.500
All right.
What are we missing?

30:15.500 --> 30:18.700
I guess we should go back and comb
through the signal spread...

30:18.700 --> 30:20.900
- check all the tracks again.
- [Monitor Beeping]

30:20.900 --> 30:25.900
Again? What's up with you two? The tracks are
clear. We ran it through every filter we've got.

30:25.900 --> 30:29.700
- That's not how magic works, Knox.
- Really, Merlin?

30:30.000 --> 30:34.000
- Then how does magic work?
- You know what? I think
we can handle it from here.

30:34.000 --> 30:37.800
- You should go home, Knox, get some rest.
- I don't want to abandon ship.

30:37.800 --> 30:41.500
It's okay. Somebody's gotta be awake enough
to run the lab tomorrow.

30:41.500 --> 30:45.800
- Seriously. Go home.
- Okay.

30:45.800 --> 30:48.000
<i>[TV: Characters Singing,</i>
<i>Indistinct]</i>

30:48.000 --> 30:50.900
<i>[Fred]</i>
<i>I love this one.</i>

30:53.500 --> 30:57.100
And even in the length
of a yo-yo string

30:57.100 --> 31:01.100
<i>There's a little bit</i>
<i>of math in everything</i>

31:01.100 --> 31:04.700
One plus one is two
and two plus two is four

31:04.700 --> 31:07.600
So how's it going
with you and Knox?

31:07.600 --> 31:11.000
- I know you were starting to...
- Started and stopped, actually.

31:11.000 --> 31:16.000
- Really?
- Yeah. We went out a few times...

31:16.000 --> 31:18.100
but I don't know...

31:18.100 --> 31:21.100
- [TV Clicks Off]
- So you stopped it?

31:21.100 --> 31:24.700
Yeah. He...
He's nice enough, but...

31:24.700 --> 31:27.200
I think he's been
working here too long.

31:27.200 --> 31:31.000
Plus, he doesn't make me laugh at all.
I mean, he tries, but...

31:31.300 --> 31:34.500
I see. You're looking
for someone funny.

31:34.500 --> 31:39.000
<i>- [Keyboard Keys Clacking]</i>
- A certain kind of funny, yeah.

31:40.400 --> 31:44.800
But I'm not really looking for
so much as looking at...

31:44.800 --> 31:48.400
Hang on.
Go back a second.

31:48.400 --> 31:52.200
- [Machine Whirring]
- There's something different.
Maybe if we bring up the volume.

31:52.200 --> 31:55.300
To the arc of a swing

31:55.300 --> 31:58.100
- And even in the length
- [No Audible Dialogue]

31:58.100 --> 32:01.900
Polo isn't singing
with the rest of them.

32:01.900 --> 32:04.900
<i>- It looks like he's talking to the audience.</i>
<i>- [Wesley] Yes.</i>

32:04.900 --> 32:07.900
<i>When the song is playing,</i>
<i>it acts as a sort of cloaking spell...</i>

32:07.900 --> 32:12.600
allowing Framkin to address his target
without being seen by the rest of his viewers.

32:12.600 --> 32:16.300
- So that's how he's been hiding it.
- That's how he <i>was</i> hiding it.

32:19.100 --> 32:21.700
[Grunting]
Stupid fingers.

32:24.400 --> 32:27.600
Stupid string.
[Grunts]

32:27.600 --> 32:32.000
It's all in the broadcast. Some very
nuanced magic, but we found it... finally.

32:32.000 --> 32:35.100
- Angel, what happened?
- Uh, nothing.

32:35.100 --> 32:38.400
It's not important.
Just doesn't matter.

32:38.400 --> 32:42.400
- Go on.
- It's a hidden carrier wave masked by a spell...

32:42.400 --> 32:45.900
that turns the TV into a two-way conduit
with direct access to the viewer.

32:45.900 --> 32:48.000
<i>[Wesley] That's how he's been</i>
<i>draining energy from the children.</i>

32:48.000 --> 32:50.600
And judging from the strength
of yesterday's signal...

32:50.600 --> 32:54.600
- Framkin's ready to take out the whole audience.
<i>- The object you described...</i>

32:54.700 --> 32:58.500
in that secret room is most likely
a repository for the children's life force.

32:58.500 --> 33:00.600
We'll have to
break the binding magic on it.

33:00.600 --> 33:05.300
Which should free those children
and reverse your puppet problem.

33:05.300 --> 33:08.100
[Joyous Gasping]
I love you guys.

33:08.100 --> 33:10.600
[Panting]

33:10.600 --> 33:14.200
Oh. [Clears Throat]
We'd better get moving.

33:14.200 --> 33:19.800
Framkin knows we're onto him. If he's ready
to zap his audience, he'll pull the trigger today.

33:19.800 --> 33:21.900
- Not him. Them.
- Gunn?

33:21.900 --> 33:24.700
<i>Framkin's not doin'this.</i>
<i>It's the puppets. They're demons.</i>

33:24.700 --> 33:28.000
The show is possessed <i>. Smile Time's</i> ratings
hit an all-time low last year.

33:28.000 --> 33:30.800
Framkin made a deal with some devils
to bring it back to number one.

33:30.800 --> 33:33.000
- You sure of that?
- Dead sure. Every contract signed...

33:33.000 --> 33:36.300
with the lower planes is filed
in the Library of Demonic Congress.

33:36.300 --> 33:39.800
You just gotta know where to look.
Pretty tricky legalese too.

33:39.800 --> 33:41.900
Framkin must have missed some
of the fine print.

33:41.900 --> 33:45.700
- Which allowed them to take over everything.
<i>- Including Framkin.</i>

33:46.000 --> 33:48.100
These particular devils
have a fairly distinctive M.O.

33:48.100 --> 33:52.100
- They've done this before?
- You seen the last few seasons of <i>Happy Days?</i>

33:52.100 --> 33:55.700
Point is, you wanna take out <i>Smile Time,</i>
take out the puppets.

33:55.700 --> 33:57.600
Well, then...

34:00.200 --> 34:02.800
let's take out some puppets.

34:18.100 --> 34:20.600
<i>[</i> Smile Time <i>Theme]</i>

34:24.800 --> 34:28.100
<i>In our secret backyard we can</i>
<i>make your day more fun and less hard</i>

34:28.100 --> 34:31.199
No more frowning
Let's get learning ABC's and 1-2-3's

34:31.199 --> 34:34.000
- Everything from words to weather
- Hi there.

34:34.000 --> 34:36.800
- Hi!
<i>- [Polo] Listen, kids.</i>

34:36.800 --> 34:40.699
Today is gonna be
an extra special, best show ever!

34:40.699 --> 34:43.600
But only if everyone at home
can give us a hand.

34:43.600 --> 34:47.100
Now, get up
and come over here.

34:47.100 --> 34:51.000
- [Characters Singing]
- [Polo] That's it, everyone.

34:51.000 --> 34:53.699
Right there.

34:53.699 --> 34:56.400
Ohh! Oh, yeah.

34:56.400 --> 35:00.200
Let it go. Let it all go.

35:00.200 --> 35:05.100
- After all, it's <i>Smile Time.!</i>
- [Angel On TV] No, it's not.

35:06.500 --> 35:10.900
It's time to kick your ass
all the way back to hell.

35:10.900 --> 35:13.300
- You!
- [Yells]

35:18.100 --> 35:20.700
Hey, man,
you're ruinin' the show!

35:20.700 --> 35:23.300
- [Gasps]
- [Squeaks]

35:23.300 --> 35:26.300
I'm workin' on it.

35:27.600 --> 35:31.100
- Angel!
- [Yelps] It's a full-scale attack!

35:31.100 --> 35:34.700
Ratio, the nest egg!

35:34.700 --> 35:37.500
[Squeaking]

35:46.400 --> 35:51.700
- [Speaking Latin]
